DESCRIPTION
Before commiting changes, format and check the code with ‘npm run lint’, and run
the tests with ‘npm t’. NO WARNINGS PERMITTED!

SERVER
When developing on the backend, first start by running ‘npm run watch’ to watch
changes on TypeScript. To run the server, use ‘npm start’ and open your browser
at the address displayed on the console.

NAMING {{{
	- observables end with $
	  (angular.io/guide/rx-library#naming-conventions-for-observables)
}}}

SERVER {{{
	- ‘npm run watch’ watches for code changes on the server
	- ‘npm start’ run the server
}}}

IMPORTS {{{
	PREFERED:
	- import { X } from 'X'
	LAST RESORT:
	- `import X from 'X'
	PROHIBITED:
	- import * as X from 'X'
	- const X = import('X')
	RESOURCES:
	- https://github.com/sourcegraph/javascript-typescript-langserver/pull/480#discussion_r197905711
	- https://github.com/Microsoft/TypeScript/issues/13340#issuecomment-348824479
	- https://github.com/DefinitelyTyped/DefinitelyTyped/issues/19337#issuecomment-364811834
	- https://github.com/microsoft/TypeScript/issues/16093
	- https://github.com/ng-packagr/ng-packagr/issues/1239
}}}

ABBREVIATIONS {{{
	- arg = argument
	- cap = capacity
	- ctx = context
	- el = element
	- ev = event
	- idx = index
	- len = length
	- msg = message
	- opt = optinal
	- pos = position
	- sz = size
}}}

KEYWORDS {{{
	- FIXME
	- NOTE
	- TODO
}}}

PONCTUATIONS {{{
	- ’ as apostrophe
	- “” for quotes
}}}

